SourceData.SourceString: The screen aligned roll of the particle in degrees.
The lifetime of a particle in seconds.

Mass is factored into the Solver Calculations (Solve Forces and Solve Rotational Forces) where forces are converted into a final velocity. The more massive a particle, the more force is required to move it.
Used to drive the Particle Random node in the Material Editor. Without this set, any Particle Randoms will get 0.0.
Distance from start of ribbon that the particle lies.
The velocity in cm/s of the particle.
The age in seconds. Useful for tracking how long a particle's been present in the scene.
The age in seconds divided by lifetime in seconds. Useful for animation as the value is between 0 and 1.
The position of the particle. This is its own type for LWC support.
The size of the sprite quad.
Sets the ribbon id for a particle. Particles with the same ribbon id will be connected into a ribbon.
Gets the bone for a random socket in the DI's filtered socket list.

Returns skinning dependant data for the pased bone in world space. Interpolated between this frame and the previous based on passed interpolation factor. All outputs are optional and you will incur zero to minimal cost if they are not connected.

Returns skinning dependant data for the pased bone in local space. Interpolated between this frame and the previous based on passed interpolation factor. All outputs are optional and you will incur zero to minimal cost if they are not connected.
